steps.instruction:
### Prep
- Thaw out the chicken
- Preheat oven to 400F
- Coat a 13x9" pan with cooking spray
- Zest or grate the lemon
    - No white about 1 tablespoon)
- Cut the bacon into small pieces
    - Put into saute pan


### Steps
1. Place the breadcrumbs into a shallow bowl
2. Coat both sides of the chicken breasts
3. Bake for 20 minutes
4. Cook the bacon on medium heat until brown and crisp 
5. Remove all but 1 tablespoon of bacon grease from the pan 
6. Combine the soup, milk and mustard until well blended
7. Pour over the chicken 
8. Sprinkle with cheese and bacon
9. Heat the bacon fat and the dressing on medium-high heat for 1 to 2 minutes
10. Add green beans and cook for 3 to 5 minutes or until crisp and tender
11. Chop olives and stir into the beans
12. Stir in the lemon zest into the beans
13. Serve
